body:
It would be nice if Verilator could support dot-style module port definition, see bold emphasis below, from the SystemVerilog LRM, Annex A.1.3.

ansi_port_declaration ::=
  [ net_port_header | interface_port_header ] port_identifier { unpacked_dimension }
  [ = constant_expression ]
  | [ variable_port_header ] port_identifier { variable_dimension } [ = constant_expression ]
  **| [ port_direction ] . port_identifier ( [ expression ] )**

Example from the LRM:
```Verilog
module mymod (
  output .P1(r[3:0]),
  output .P2(r[7:4]),
  ref .Y(x),
  input R
);
  logic [7:0] r;
  int x;
  // ...
endmodule
```

